Professor Emeritus '''James W. Gair''' (December 27, 1927 – December 10, 2016)<ref name="CU obit">{{cite web|title=James W. Gair (1927–2016) |url=https://sap.einaudi.cornell.edu/james-w-gair-obituary |publisher=[[Cornell University]] |accessdate=March 25, 2017}}</ref> was a linguist in South Asian linguistics. He was a specialist in [[Sinhala language|Sinhala]], as well as in [[Pali language|Pali]], [[Tamil language|Tamil]] and [[Dhivehi language|Dhivehi]].<ref name="Cornell News">[http://www.news.cornell.edu/stories/2017/01/james-w-gair-linguistics-professor-emeritus-dies-88  James W. Gair, linguistics professor emeritus, dies at 88 - Cornell University]</ref> He taught in the Department of Modern Languages and Linguistics of Cornell University (Ithaca, New York). later the Department of Linguistics.  He died right before his 89th birthday on December 10, 2016.<ref name="Cornell News"/>

